\pard\b\fs30 1 Concept and architecture\b0\fs22\par
\pard\b 1.1 Purpose and scope\b0\par
\pard THOG2 replaces repeated dense transformer-block matrices with compact learned coefficient tensors. Those coefficients, together with deterministic orthogonal bases, regenerate layer-specific dense-equivalent weights on demand. Dense remains a control path; this document covers the non-dense compact geometries only.\par
\pard The purpose of this specification is not merely to list presets. It is to impose a coherent geometry grammar so that compact-depth, generic sheet, MLP block, head-aware block, full block, and the new semantic sheet variants are not implemented as disconnected historical artefacts.\par

\pard\b 1.2 Core compact-depth idea\b0\par
\pard Layer depth is the privileged axis. In all compact geometries, the depth basis describes how a repeated matrix family changes across transformer layers. A depth-only geometry compresses only this layer axis. A sheet geometry compresses depth plus one matrix axis. A block geometry compresses depth plus both matrix axes. A semantic sheet geometry compresses depth plus one semantically selected matrix axis while leaving other semantic axes whole.\par
\pard This distinction matters. A weak run from a geometry that changes several choices at once cannot tell us which choice failed. BLOCK changed both semantic specialization and bilinear matrix-axis compression. The semantic sheet ladder is therefore designed as controlled ablations.\par

\pard\b 1.3 Axis discipline and clean-axis rule\b0\par
\pard Every compact geometry shall state which axes are compressed and which axes remain whole. QKV role, attention head, local head channel, MLP hidden channel, and residual d_model channel are different semantic axes. Generic geometries may flatten axes. Semantic geometries shall preserve their declared semantic axes whole.\par
\pard No semantic sheet preset shall introduce basis sharing across qkv_role or attention head. No semantic MLP sheet preset shall introduce basis sharing across hidden_channel. Any future violation of this rule must be named as a separate experiment rather than hidden inside an existing preset.\par

\pard\b 1.4 Integrated resolver model\b0\par
\pard The old two-slot abstraction, preset to attention_geometry plus mlp_geometry, is not sufficient for the semantic sheet ladder. QKV and attention output require separate component choices. The implementation shall therefore resolve each compact preset into three component slots: mlp_component, qkv_component, and attn_out_component.\par
\pard Existing geometries remain first-class. The resolver shall route legacy_sheet_col, generic_sheet_col, depth, mlp_block, head_aware_block, and full_block through the same catalogue as sheet_mlp, sheet_qkv, sheet_out_dmodel, sheet_out_local, sheet_full_dmodel, and sheet_full_local.\par

\pard\b\fs30 2 Definitions and notation\b0\fs22\par
\pard\b 2.1 Dimension symbols\b0\par
\pard\f2 L\tab number of transformer layers\par
\pard D\tab residual model width, n_embd\par
\pard H\tab number of attention heads\par
\pard Dh\tab head dimension, D/H\par
\pard M\tab MLP hidden width, 4D\par
\pard P\tab depth order, o_depth\par
\pard Q\tab attention/residual d_model order, o_attn_d_model\par
\pard J\tab QKV local-head-channel order, o_attn_qkv_per_channel\par
\pard O\tab attention-output local-head-channel order, o_attn_out_per_channel\par
\pard X\tab MLP d_model order, o_mlp_d_model\par
\pard Y\tab MLP hidden order, o_mlp_hidden\f0\par

\pard\b 2.2 Matrix families\b0\par
\pard The repeated matrix families are attention_input_weight or the split semantic Q/K/V weights, attention_output_weight, mlp_expansion_weight, and mlp_contraction_weight. PyTorch Linear uses weight shape [out_features, in_features], so rows are output-channel recipes over input channels.\par
\pard MLP expansion has dense shape W_up[M,D]. MLP contraction has dense shape W_down[D,M]. QKV has dense semantic shape W_qkv[qkv_role, head, local_head_channel, d_model_input]. Attention output has dense semantic shape W_out[d_model_output, head, local_head_channel].\par

\pard\b 2.3 Basis families and compact orders\b0\par
\pard Supported compact basis families are Chebyshev and DCT. The basis family and basis version are part of compact identity. Dense/conventional is a separate control path and shall not masquerade as compact.\par

