\pard\b 3.2 Existing compact geometries\b0\par
\pard depth uses coefficient shape coeff[out,in,P] for matrix families. It is closest to giving every dense-equivalent scalar weight its own depth polynomial. It is intentionally expensive in coefficient count but semantically conservative.\par
\pard generic_sheet_col is the current legacy sheet-column geometry. It uses one sheet per output row and compresses depth plus input columns. For QKV this leaves packed output rows whole, so role/head/local output channels are not compressed on the output side. For attention output, input_cols are flattened head times local_head_channel and are compressed as one generic axis.\par
\pard generic_sheet_row is the transposed generic ablation. It uses one sheet per input column and compresses depth plus output rows. It is required because DEPTH approximately matching legacy_sheet_col does not by itself prove that whole output rows are the right generic choice.\par
\pard mlp_block compresses both matrix axes for MLP matrices. head_aware_block keeps attention head whole and compresses per-head/channel axes. full_block combines head-aware attention with MLP block.\par

\pard\b 3.3 New semantic sheet geometries\b0\par
\pard sheet_mlp keeps hidden_channel whole for both MLP expansion and contraction, while compressing depth plus the residual d_model side. This is the main semantic MLP ablation and differs from generic sheet mainly on MLP contraction.\par
\pard sheet_qkv keeps qkv_role, head, and local_head_channel whole while compressing depth plus d_model_input. This avoids smearing Q/K/V role or head identity.\par
\pard sheet_out_dmodel keeps head and local_head_channel whole while compressing depth plus d_model_output. sheet_out_local keeps d_model_output and head whole while compressing depth plus local_head_channel. Both are required because attention output is the least obvious axis-choice case.\par

\pard\b 3.4 Order consumption\b0\par
\pard\f2 depth: P\par
\pard generic_sheet_col: P + q_in\par
\pard generic_sheet_row: P + q_out\par
\pard mlp_block: P + X + Y\par
\pard head_aware_block_qkv: P + J + Q\par
\pard head_aware_block_out: P + Q + O\par
\pard sheet_mlp: P + X\par
\pard sheet_qkv: P + Q\par
\pard sheet_out_dmodel: P + Q\par
\pard sheet_out_local: P + O\f0\par

