\pard\b 4.2 Serious first-run ablation set\b0\par
\pard The serious first-run set shall include generic_sheet_col, generic_sheet_row, depth, sheet_mlp, sheet_qkv, sheet_attn_dmodel, sheet_attn_local, sheet_full_dmodel, and sheet_full_local. Other combinations are useful diagnostics but lower priority.\par

\pard\b\fs30 5 Exact coefficient-shape requirements\b0\fs22\par
\pard\f1\fs18
Component\tab Dense semantic shape\tab Coefficient shape\par
\pard depth\tab W[out,in]\tab coeff[out,in,P]\par
\pard generic_sheet_col\tab W[out,in]\tab coeff[out,P,q_in]\par
\pard generic_sheet_row\tab W[out,in]\tab coeff[in,P,q_out]\par
\pard mlp_block up\tab W_up[M,D]\tab coeff[P,Y,X]\par
\pard mlp_block down\tab W_down[D,M]\tab coeff[P,X,Y]\par
\pard head_aware_block Q/K/V\tab W[head,Dh,D]\tab coeff[head,P,J,Q] per role family\par
\pard head_aware_block out\tab W[D,head,Dh]\tab coeff[head,P,Q,O]\par
\pard sheet_mlp up\tab W_up[hidden,d_model_input]\tab coeff[hidden,P,X]\par
\pard sheet_mlp down\tab W_down[d_model_output,hidden]\tab coeff[hidden,P,X]\par
\pard sheet_qkv\tab W[qkv_role,head,local_head_channel,d_model_input]\tab coeff[qkv_role,head,local_head_channel,P,Q]\par
\pard sheet_out_dmodel\tab W[d_model_output,head,local_head_channel]\tab coeff[head,local_head_channel,P,Q]\par
\pard sheet_out_local\tab W[d_model_output,head,local_head_channel]\tab coeff[d_model_output,head,P,O]\f0\fs22\par

\pard Materialisation formulas shall be explicit in implementation comments/tests. Generic sheet-col: W_l[o,i] = sum_pq coeff[o,p,q] B_depth[l,p] B_in[i,q]. Depth: W_l[o,i] = sum_p coeff[o,i,p] B_depth[l,p]. Block: W_l[o,i] = sum_pab coeff[p,a,b] B_depth[l,p] B_out[o,a] B_in[i,b].\par

\pard\b\fs30 6 Resolver, identity, aliases, and checkpoint policy\b0\fs22\par
\pard The implementation shall expose a resolved geometry object with: requested_preset, canonical_preset, mlp_component, qkv_component, attn_out_component, basis_family, basis_version, consumed_orders, and coefficient_families. QKV and attention-output are separate slots.\par
\pard New runs shall store both requested_preset and canonical_preset. legacy_sheet_col shall remain accepted indefinitely as an input alias for generic_sheet_col. curve shall remain accepted as an input alias for depth. Existing checkpoints using legacy names shall remain loadable unless the branch is explicitly declared checkpoint-breaking. New artifact names shall prefer canonical names unless compatibility mode requires otherwise.\par
\pard The component validity matrix is: MLP slot accepts depth, generic_sheet_col, generic_sheet_row, mlp_block, sheet_mlp. QKV slot accepts depth, generic_sheet_col, generic_sheet_row, head_aware_block_qkv, sheet_qkv. Attention-output slot accepts depth, generic_sheet_col, generic_sheet_row, head_aware_block_out, sheet_out_dmodel, sheet_out_local. Mixed dense/compact inside a non-dense preset is forbidden unless separately approved.\par

\pard\b\fs30 7 Correctness, reporting, and tests\b0\fs22\par
\pard For every compact component, direct/factorised execution and materialise-then-linear execution, where both exist, shall produce equivalent outputs within dtype-appropriate tolerance. Forward and backward tests shall prove gradients reach the relevant coefficient tensors.\par
\pard Parameter reporting shall expose persistent_parameters, coefficient_parameters, dense_equivalent_parameters, per-family coefficient shapes, per-family dense-equivalent shapes, consumed compact orders, requested and canonical preset names, and resolved components.\par
\pard Tests shall be descriptive and cover alias resolution, preset composition, coefficient shapes, parameter counts, materialisation equivalence, checkpoint identity, wrapper dry-runs, and CPU forward/backward smoke tests for each new component.\par

\pard\b\fs30 8 Implementation plan\b0\fs22\par
\pard\b 8.1 Preliminary integration pass\b0\par
\pard First, canonicalise names without changing model math: legacy_sheet_col becomes an alias for generic_sheet_col, and curve remains an alias for depth. Then replace the current two-slot resolver spine with the three-component resolved object. Existing geometries shall route through this resolver before any new semantic sheet implementation begins.\par
\pard\b 8.2 Descriptor layer\b0\par
\pard Introduce semantic family descriptors for MLP expansion, MLP contraction, QKV, and attention output. Each descriptor shall declare dense semantic shape, compressed axes, whole axes, consumed orders, coefficient shape, materialisation recipe, initialization policy, and parameter-count contribution.\par
\pard\b 8.3 Existing geometry migration\b0\par
\pard Route generic_sheet_col, depth, mlp_block, head_aware_block, and full_block through the new catalogue while preserving existing working code paths. Do not delete old paths; comment out only when necessary and mark THOG changes according to project convention.\par
\pard\b 8.4 New components\b0\par
\pard Implement generic_sheet_row first because it is a pure generic orientation ablation. Then implement sheet_mlp, sheet_qkv, sheet_out_dmodel, and sheet_out_local as components. After component tests pass, expose the composed public presets.\par
\pard\b 8.5 Release gates\b0\par
\pard Gates: compileall, bash -n wrappers, focused resolver tests, coefficient shape tests, materialisation equivalence tests, forward/backward gradient tests, parameter-report tests, wrapper dry-run tests, and the existing repository regression suite. No GPU-performance claims are made without a real GPU run.\par

\pard\b\fs30 9 Non-goals\b0\fs22\par
\pard This stage does not attempt kernel fusion, sparse kernels, checkpoint migration, or attention replacement. It does not claim that semantic sheet will outperform dense. The purpose is to make the geometry experiment clean enough that failures are interpretable.\par
